cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based architecture for multimodal classification tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper deals with cross-modal information and partial absence of data, which suggests that it may belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the proposed architecture and the datasets used in the experiments involve image and text modalities.
